                                                               The Hall\u8211?Petch breakdown\par
                                                               For coarse-grained specimens, the preceding discussion\par
                                                               demonstrates that the grain-size strengthening increment\par
                                                               can be estimated using equation (1) and the constants in\par
                                                               Table 1, and that much of the variation among the differ-\par
                                                               ent studies can be explained by some combination of\par
                                                               specimen contamination and work-hardening effects.\par
                                                               However, data from a few of the datasets in Figs. 1\u8211?3\par
                                                               (most notably that for Zn and Cu) illustrate that simply\par
                                                               extrapolating the grain-size strengthening behaviour of\par
                                                               coarse-grained samples to nanocrystalline grain sizes\par
                                                               can result in errors: the strength measured in the \u64257?nest\par
                                                               grain-size specimens can be less than that expected.225,226\par
                                                               This apparent breakdown of the Hall\u8211?Petch effect has\par
                                                               been much discussed and debated, and it is clear that\par
                                                               many of the observations of lowered strength levels in\par
                                                               nanograined materials can be attributed to artefacts in\par
                                                               sample processing. At the same time, it is physically\par
                                                               reasonable that the Hall\u8211?Petch equation breaks down;\par
