                                                                            Summary and outlook\par
                                                                            In this work, we calculated best estimates of the pure\par
                                                                            metals\u8217? Hall\u8211?Petch parameters using the grain-size\par
                                                                            strengthening data accumulated over the past six decades.\par
                                                                            We also used these data to validate the Hall\u8211?Petch coef\u64257?-\par
                                                                            cient\u8217?s dependence on crystal structure, the similarities\par
                                                                            between the frictional stress and single crystal \u64258?ow stress\par
                                                                            and several other trends. Some of these trends are\par
                                                                            accounted for in the dislocation pile-up model of grain-\par
                                                                            size strengthening, but as we have noted, there is no direct\par
                                                                            evidence to support this model\u8217?s underlying assumption\par
                                                                            that the grain-size limits the size of dislocation pile-ups.\par
                                                                            Though the other explanations of grain-size strengthening\par
                                                                            that we summarized also have de\u64257?ciencies, Ashby\u8217?s\par
                                                                            geometrically necessary dislocation model appears to be\par
                                                                            the most consistent with the strain-dependence of the\par
                                                                            Hall\u8211?Petch coef\u64257?cient and with experimental obser-\par
                                                                            vations of the dislocation substructure in plastically\par
                                                                            deformed polycrystals with coarse grain sizes.\par
                                                                               Our compilation of grain-size strengthening measure-\par
                                                                            ments revealed several gaps in the open literature that\par
                                                                            should be addressed in future research. In addition to\par
